      • assignIdToElement

        public void assignIdToElement(String locator,
                              String id)
        Assigns the id to the element located by locator.

        This is useful in situations where we need to assign a temporary id to an element to refer it later.
        Assigned id is temporary and will be reset if page refreshed or navigation happens
        Parameters:
        locator - the locator to locate the element
        id - the id to assign

        public void elementTextShouldBe(String locator,
                                String text,

        Verify the element text identified by locator is equal to text.
